{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.18",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 18,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 18 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:1",
      "text": "He who lives forever created the whole universe.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:2",
      "text": "The Lord alone is just.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:4",
      "text": "He has given power to declare his works to no one. Who could trace out his mighty deeds?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:5",
      "text": "Who could measure the strength of his majesty? Who could also proclaim his mercies?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:6",
      "text": "As for the wondrous works of the Lord, it is not possible to take from them nor add to them, neither is it possible to explore them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:7",
      "text": "When a man has finished, then he is just at the beginning. When he stops, then he will be perplexed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:8",
      "text": "What is mankind, and what purpose do they serve? What is their good, and what is their evil?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:9",
      "text": "The number of man’s days at the most are a hundred years.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:10",
      "text": "As a drop of water from the sea, and a pebble from the sand, so are a few years in the day of eternity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:11",
      "text": "For this cause the Lord was patient over them, and poured out his mercy upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:12",
      "text": "He saw and perceived their end, that it is evil. Therefore he multiplied his forgiveness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:13",
      "text": "The mercy of a man is on his neighbor; but the mercy of the Lord is on all flesh: reproving, chastening, teaching, and bringing back, as a shepherd does his flock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:14",
      "text": "He has mercy on those who accept chastening, and that diligently seek after his judgments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:15",
      "text": "My son, don’t add reproach to your good deeds, and no harsh words in any of your giving.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:16",
      "text": "Doesn’t the dew relieve the scorching heat? So a word is better than a gift.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:17",
      "text": "Behold, isn’t a word better than a gift? Both are with a gracious person.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:18",
      "text": "A fool is ungracious and abusive. The gift of a grudging person consumes the eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:19",
      "text": "Learn before you speak. Take care of your health before you get sick.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:20",
      "text": "Before judgment, examine yourself, and in the hour of scrutiny you will find forgiveness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:21",
      "text": "Humble yourself before you get sick. In the time of sins, repent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:22",
      "text": "Let nothing hinder you to pay your vow in due time. Don’t wait until death to be released.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:23",
      "text": "Before you make a vow, prepare yourself. Don’t be like a man who tests the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:24",
      "text": "Think about the wrath coming in the days of the end, and the time of vengeance, when he turns away his face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:25",
      "text": "In the days of fullness remember the time of hunger. Remember poverty and lack in the days of wealth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:26",
      "text": "From morning until evening, the time changes. All things are speedy before the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:27",
      "text": "A wise man is cautious in everything. In days of sinning, he will beware of offense.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:28",
      "text": "Every man of understanding knows wisdom. He will give thanks to him who found her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:29",
      "text": "They who were of understanding in sayings also became wise themselves, and poured out apt proverbs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:30",
      "text": "Don’t go after your lusts. Restrain your appetites.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:31",
      "text": "If you give fully to your soul the delight of her desire, she will make you the laughing stock of your enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:32",
      "text": "Don’t make merry in much luxury, and don’t be tied to its expense.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.18.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:33",
      "text": "Don’t be made a beggar by banqueting with borrowed money when you have nothing in your purse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
